  "text": "With the help of moments, one can find the mean, variance, skewness, kurtosis, etc of a distribution. The underlying distribution can also be determined by its moment sequence. Campbell [CITATION_1] gave a lower bound for the normalized cumulants in terms of Rényi entropy.",
